      "text": "4 (0.1) The registrar is responsible for supporting accessibility in the passenger directed vehicle industry. (0.2) For the purposes of subsection (0.1), the registrar may make payments to licensees, the drivers of passenger directed vehicles, and prescribed persons or organizations. (1) Without limiting section 2 (3), the registrar may (a) maintain an electronic or other index identifying licensees and permit holders and setting out the status of their respective licences and temporary operating permits, (b) make the index available to the public in any manner that the registrar considers appropriate, and (c) make rules of procedure respecting all applications, submissions and matters coming before the registrar. (3) The registrar may delegate the registrar's powers, functions and duties as set out in this section, including the powers under sections 46, 47 and 48 and under Part 4.",
