      "text": "25 (1) If the registrar receives an application for a licence in which the only authorization sought is a general authorization, the registrar must, subject to subsections (1.1), (4) and (5), issue a licence and provide it to the applicant, if the registrar is satisfied that the applicant holds a valid safety certificate if required and meets prescribed requirements; proof of financial responsibility has been or will be given or the applicable motor vehicle liability policies have been or will be issued; the applicant will ensure motor vehicles meet prescribed requirements; and the applicant is not subject to an order under Part 6. (1.1) The registrar may consider whether the applicant is a fit and proper person to provide the service and refuse to issue a licence if the applicant is not. (2.1) The registrar must establish as a term or condition of a licence that each motor vehicle operated under the licence must display a vehicle identifier issued to the licensee by the registrar or authorized by the registrar to be issued by the licensee. (3) If a licence is issued under this section, the licensee is, subject to section 23 (1), authorized to operate each of the motor vehicles to which the licence applies as general passenger vehicles. (4) If the registrar believes that the operations intended by the applicant require a special authorization, the registrar must forward the application to the board. (5) After receiving the application, the board must determine whether a special authorization is required and notify the registrar and applicant accordingly.",
