      "id": "pta-s28",
      "number": "28",
      "text": "28 (1) The board may approve, in whole or in part, an application forwarded under section 26 (1) after considering (a) whether the applicant is a fit and proper person to provide the service and is capable of providing the service; and (b) if so, whether there is a public need for the service and whether the application, if granted, would promote sound economic conditions in the passenger transportation industry in British Columbia. (2) If the board approves an application, the board must specify the special authorizations that should be included in the licence. (3) The board may establish terms and conditions that apply to a special authorization, including respecting equipment or technology; routes and minimum route frequencies for inter-city bus authorizations; methods of hailing, information display, fleet size and geographic area for passenger directed vehicle authorizations; and information, fleet size and geographic area for transportation network services authorizations. (4) The board must establish as a term or condition that each motor vehicle operated under the authorization display a vehicle identifier. (5) The board must establish as a term or condition that the licensee provide to the registrar information and data the registrar or board may require, including about the motor vehicles and drivers, availability for hailing, and trip data. (6) The board must establish as a term or condition of a transportation network services authorization that motor vehicles may be hailed only through the transportation network services approved. (7) The board must notify the registrar and applicant of its decision and, if approved, the terms and conditions established.",
